---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Compare Affiliate Platforms Before You Commit";
const description = "Compare affiliate platforms using practical criteria, evaluating payouts, reliability, and true fit without getting distracted by hype.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-900 border-b border-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-gray-400">Before you commit a significant amount of content and traffic to a platform, it helps to compare the criteria that actually affect long-term viability.</p>
      <div class="mt-10">
        <a href="#compare" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Compare top options now</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Choosing the right network is an architectural decision.</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">Many people focus on the wrong signal first—such as finding the network with the largest volume of merchants—and end up with terrible tracking unreliability or payment delays. Trust, tracking methodology, and withdrawal thresholds matter deeply.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">A better choice usually comes down to fit:</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-8">
        <li>how reliable is their link tracking and cookie duration?</li>
        <li>how long does it take for payouts to clear?</li>
        <li>what are the support channels like if a tracking failure occurs?</li>
        <li>is the platform focused on your specific niche industry?</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">What You’ll Find on This Page</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">On this page, you’ll find a clearer way to evaluate your network options, compare common industry platforms, and move toward committing to a reliable partner.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Who This Is For</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-4">This page is a good fit if you:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>are comparing networks like ShareASale, CJ Affiliate, or Impact</li>
        <li>are preparing to centralize your affiliate effort on one or two platforms</li>
        <li>want to understand the trade-offs of independent in-house programs versus aggregate networks</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">This may be less useful if you are entirely locked into the Amazon Associates ecosystem and don't plan on exploring elsewhere.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Why This Direction Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">Instead of choosing based on surface-level claims of huge brand catalogs, you can evaluate platforms using more practical criteria like average reversal rates, ease of link building, and API accessibility. Less guesswork, deeper reliability.</p>

      <h2 id="compare" class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Compare Affiliate Platforms</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-gray-400">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-700 text-white">
              <th class="py-3 px-4">Platform Type</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4">Strength</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4">Trade-off</th>
              <th class="py-3 px-4">Best For</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-700">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Mass Market / Aggregate (e.g., ShareASale, Rakuten)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Thousands of physical product brands, central payout</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Outdated UI, disjointed merchant approval</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Lifestyle, fashion, general B2C</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-700">
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Independent SaaS (e.g., Rewardful, PartnerStack)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Direct relationships, high recurring revenue</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Must track payouts uniquely per software</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">B2B, tech tools, software reviewers</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">CPA exclusivity (e.g., MaxBounty)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Extremely high payouts for lead gen</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Fiercely guarded approval, strict compliance</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">High-volume media buyers and email lists</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Trust & Rationale</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-8">The goal here is not to label one option as universally “best.” It’s to help you compare the right variables so you can choose what fits your niche, workflow, and goals more confidently. Fit and reliability matter far more than vanity metrics.</p>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-400 text-lg mb-12">
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">How should I compare these options?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Look at the payout friction. Are their commission reversals high? Is the threshold $50 or $500? Evaluate them on how easy it is to actually see your money.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">What trade-offs should I watch for?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">Large networks give you centralized payments but terrible support. In-house programs have excellent support from the host company but make accounting significantly harder.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">Where should I start if I’m unsure?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">If you merely want to get your feet wet, find one massive network (or Amazon) and experiment just to learn content-to-conversion flow before heavily integrating API-based platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong class="text-white">What related page should I read after this?</strong>
          <p class="mt-2">If you are moving to higher margins, read about <a href="/offers/high-ticket-affiliate-programs" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">high-ticket affiliate programs</a> and why they are often self-hosted or strictly managed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-xl p-8 border border-gray-700 text-center mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Find Your Partner Ecosystem</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mb-6">Stop guessing and review key differences between affiliate networks.</p>
        <a href="/programs" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-lg transition-colors">Choose your best-fit platform</a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Related Resources</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-400 text-lg space-y-3 mb-8">
        <li><a href="/blog/how-to-compare-affiliate-platforms" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">How to Compare Affiliate Platforms Without Getting Lost in the Marketing</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/what-makes-a-high-ticket-affiliate-program-worth-promoting" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">What Makes a High-Ticket Affiliate Program Actually Worth Promoting?</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/high-ticket-vs-recurring-affiliate-programs" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">High-Ticket vs Recurring Affiliate Programs</a></li>
        <li><a href="/offers/find-your-best-affiliate-fit" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Find your best affiliate fit</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
